<p>&#8220;&#8230;when I hear of an author who cannot finish or get started on a book, I send him (or her) a rhino card. I paint a watercolor of a rhinoceros on the front of a postcard&#8211;something I do well, as I&#39;ve practiced it a great many times. And in the space next to the address I write: &#8220;Stop fussing about that book. Just charge it. Keep on charging it until it is finished. That&#39;s what the rhino does. Put this card over your desk and remember the Rhino Principle.&#8221;</p>
