  <li id="comment-36140" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/06903398489768100311" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Rebecca</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/12/in-my-better-moments/#comment-36140"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-12-15T16:04:41-05:00">Thursday, December 15, 2011 at 4:04 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My husband (a very good and quite successful screenwriter) once walked in on me having a freak out about how bad my writing was. He went away and came back five minutes later with a piece of paper that he taped up opposite my desk. It says: </p>
<p>THE FIRST DRAFT IS ALWAYS SHIT. </p>
<p>And every time I freak out, I look at that and it eases the self-imposed pressure. &lt;3</p>
    </div>

