  <li id="comment-36146" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/07824123805925551656" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">nomadshan</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/12/in-my-better-moments/#comment-36146"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-12-15T16:46:06-05:00">Thursday, December 15, 2011 at 4:46 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Early drafts are meant to be crap. Well, they&#39;re meant to allow you to throw spaghetti strands at the wall and see what sticks, so the resulting mess often looks terrible. Embrace revision &#8212; that&#39;s when you can put text where it should be, make meaningful connections, polish your word choices, and ditch the rest. Best of luck!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-36146' data-commentid="36146" data-postid="455" data-belowelement="comment-36146" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to nomadshan" aria-label='Reply to nomadshan'>Reply</a>    </div>
