  <li id="comment-36219" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09643317297830165273" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Julie</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/12/in-my-better-moments/#comment-36219"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-12-19T14:32:13-05:00">Monday, December 19, 2011 at 2:32 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love On Writing. One of King&#39;s most memorably passages for me was regarding the position of a writer&#39;s desk&#8211;facing the wall, not gazing out the window. When I was setting up our office, that&#39;s exactly what I did. (I do have the window immediately to my left, and a swivel chair, so I&#39;m afraid I still spend much time bird- and neighbor watching.)</p>
<p>Keep the faith&#8211;your book will be fabulous, and we all can&#39;t wait to read it!</p>
    </div>

